Responses to women’s leadership were mixed as respondents did not appear to understand the principal objective of women’s forums, which was to train and help them organize and advocate for their rights. Reluctant male participants reiterate these perceptions that their leadership was natural – a result of being a man. In the words of Charles Sikoﬀ, “slavery disguised as empowerment. ‘We brought her here, so we can let her go if we want’.” Low female enrollment and high dropout rates were widely reported.
